%N A279069 Smallest k such that 1 + p + p^2 + p^3 + ... + p^k is prime, where p is the n-th prime.
%C A279069 Equivalently, smallest k such that (p^(k+1)-1)/(p-1) is prime, where p is the n-th prime.
